cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.IR

The paper proposes a novel approach for view imputation using generative adversarial networks (GANs) and denoising autoencoders (DAEs). This approach falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves training GANs and DAEs to learn mappings between different views of data. Additionally, the use of GANs suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The application of the proposed approach in a genetic study of substance use disorders suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
